SQL Joins (INNER JOIN)
1️⃣ What is INNER JOIN?

INNER JOIN returns only the matching rows from both tables based on a related column.

Think of it like:

Table A → Employees

Table B → Departments

The common column → department_id

Only employees that have a matching department will appear in the result.

2️⃣ Example Tables
Employees Table
employee_id	name	department_id
1	John	101
2	Sarah	102
3	Mike	103
4	Anna	101
Departments Table
department_id	department_name
101	HR
102	IT
103	Finance
3️⃣ INNER JOIN Syntax
SELECT column_names
FROM table1
INNER JOIN table2
ON table1.common_column = table2.common_column;


SELECT employees.name, departments.department_name
FROM employees
INNER JOIN departments
on employee.department_id=departments.department_id;


output
name	department_name
John	HR
Sarah	IT
Mike	Finance
Anna	HR
ON employees.department_id = departments.department_id;
